:name: XIAO nRF52840 single (T0 boot / T1 Studio RPC over UART)
:description: Boot one XIAO nRF52840 ZMK image; console on uart0, Studio RPC on uart1.

# Console (banner, logs) is on uart0; ZMK Studio RPC is on uart1 (see
# overlays/studio-rpc-uart.overlay — this is the Renode stand-in for USB
# Studio RPC, see references/renode-notes.md). Both UARTs are exposed as
# separate TCP server-socket terminals so a Python harness can attach to
# each independently. This script only loads the ELF and wires the UARTs;
# it does NOT call `start` — the harness starts the emulation explicitly
# (over the monitor `-P` port) only after it has connected to both UART
# sockets, so no early boot-banner bytes are lost.

using sysbus

$bin?=@zmk.elf
$console_port?=3455
$rpc_port?=3456

mach create "single"
machine LoadPlatformDescription @platforms/xiao_nrf52840.repl

emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $console_port "console_term" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart0 console_term

emulation CreateServerSocketTerminal $rpc_port "rpc_term" false
connector Connect sysbus.uart1 rpc_term

sysbus LoadELF $bin
